article.headline: Vermont 67, Northeastern 65
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Matt Jensen and reigning American East player of the year Taylor Coppenrath each had 18 points to lead Vermont past Northeastern, 67-65, on Sunday. Northeastern went on an 18-6 run late in the second half and tied the score at 63 with 1:05 left in the game, but T.J. Sorrentine nailed a 3-pointer with 52 seconds left to secure the win. The Catamounts (15-5, 11-0) tied a school record with their 12th straight win. Jose Juan Barea, who had a game-high 28 points, missed a layup and a 3-pointer in the last 10 seconds of the game for the Huskies (14-9, 8-4). Sorrentine finished with 13 points and Germain Njila had 11 for the Catamounts, who took their biggest lead of the game when Jensen hit one of his six 3-pointers to go up 57-45 with 7:30 left in the second half. David Hehn had 13 rebounds and Martin Klimes had 10 rebounds for Vermont, which outrebounded Northeastern, 46-35, and had 13 second-chance points in the second half. Coppenrath, who was double teamed for the entire game, sparked an 11-point Vermont run to start the second half that erased Northeastern's 30-25 halftime lead. The Catamounts never trailed after Coppenrath scored six straight points in a span of 1:30, putting Vermont up, 32-30, on a layup at the 18:20 mark. Bobby Kelly scored 12 for Northeastern and Javorie Wilson shot just 3-of-14 from the field for 10 points in the losing effort.
